cubes.name: EditedAlleleCallID
cubes.title: Edited Allele Call
cubes.description: A concatenation of Sample ID Product 360 (p360) curated reference assembly including the chromosome or contig pollux ID identifying the guide used coordinate of the guide on the reference assembly and local_CIGAR. This makes this effectively a UUID for SME2.

measures.name: EditedAlleleCallID.count_distinct_edited_allele_call_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Call Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID

measures.name: EditedAlleleCallID.sum_of_allele_call_read_count
measures.title: Edited Allele Call Total Allele Call Reads
measures.description: This is to get sum of Allele Call Read Counts

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.edited_allele_call_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Edited Allele Call ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of Sample ID Product 360 (p360) curated reference assembly including the chromosome or contig pollux ID identifying the guide used coordinate of the guide on the reference assembly and local_CIGAR. This makes this effectively a UUID for SME2.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.edited_allele_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Edited Allele ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of reference name identifier with chromosome (contig) 5' coordinate start of guide and local CIGAR.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.call_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.sample_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Sample ID
dimensions.description: The Sample ID as designated by the LIMS system note is a concatenation of underscore separated SEQID and sample number.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.barcode
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Barcode
dimensions.description: Barcode refers to the plant barcode or gds barcode as provided from LIMS and importantly is sample specific.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.reagent
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Reagent
dimensions.description: This generally refers to constructs or pMONs but in the future could indicate other methodologies for introducing foreign DNA.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.guide_name
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Guide Name
dimensions.description: Pollux ID from SeqUR for the guide used to create this edit.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.allele_call_read_count
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Allele Call Read Counts
dimensions.description: Count of reads with this allele call covering the guide window.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.percent_of_reads_covering_guide
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Percent Reads
dimensions.description: Percentage of reads covering the guide with this exact allele. Calculated as allele_call_read_count over total_reads_covering_guide.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.hamming_distance
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Hamming Distance
dimensions.description: Number of differences between two sequences of the same length in this case the reference sequence and aligned read sequence.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.allele_call_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Allele Call Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleCallID.Allele_Call_sequencing_run
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Call Sequence Run ID
dimensions.description: The run identifier from the sequencer that this project was ran on for backtracking and unifying with sequencing QC.

cubes.name: EditedAlleleID
cubes.title: Edited Allele
cubes.description: Schema for the edited allele table, containing information about reference identifiers, sequences, and alignment details.

measures.name: EditedAlleleID.count_distinct_edited_allele_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.edited_allele_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Edited Allele ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of reference name identifier with chromosome (contig) 5' coordinate start of guide and local CIGAR.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.allele_type
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Allele Type
dimensions.description: Type of allele, one of 'edit', 'wt', or 'offsite'.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.edited_allele_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.fp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Five Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Five prime sequence which is the sequence upstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.tp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Three Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Three prime sequence which is the sequence downstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.ref_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Reference string
dimensions.description: The wild-type or reference sequence of the guide region.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.match_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Sequence Match string
dimensions.description: The sequence of the read aligned segment for the allele.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.allele_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Allele Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: Compact idiosyncratic gapped alignment report for the entire read with respect to the edited allele.

dimensions.name: EditedAlleleID.local_CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: The CIGAR localized to the guide region including notation for contiguous edits outside the guide window.
dimensions.shortTitle: Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)

cubes.name: capacity_request
cubes.title: Capacity Request
cubes.description: Capacity Request in Velocity is a workflow designed to enable researchers to request space for  experimental or seed production workflows in Open Fields, Controlled Environments, and Labs across Bayer's Crop Science business units. It offers various functionalities, including creating new requests, saving requests in draft mode,  and checking the status of existing requests. It stores information for all the capacity requests.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each capacity request made within the Capacity Request workflow in the Velocity application This ID helps users track and manage their requests effectively throughout the process.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.approval_flag
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Approval Flag
dimensions.description: The true indicates the submitted capacity request has been approved, false indicates the submitted capacity request is not approved

dimensions.name: capacity_request.border_plots
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Border Plots
dimensions.description: This gives the number of border plots

dimensions.name: capacity_request.checks
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Checks
dimensions.description: The number of commercial Checks on the Capacity Request. Checks are defined as Bayer or Competitor products  that are added to experimental or observational trials to either compare against trial entries or  normalize data for environment or year effects. Based on the trial requirements, different types of checks are utilized.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.crop_material_stage
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Crop Stage Name
dimensions.description: It specific phase or step within the product development pipeline for example Commercial,Pre-Commercial 0, Pre-Commercial 2,Pre-Commercial 2.5, Pre-Commercial 3,Pre-Commercial 4, Mixed PCM Stages, Level 1, Level 2, Level 4, Entry Level, Screening 0,Screening 1,Screening 2, Screening 2 - Prep, Screening 2 - Test,Germplasm Development, Pipeline Unrelated etc

dimensions.name: capacity_request.crops
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Crops
dimensions.description: The name of the crop. For example Corn, Rice, Cotton, Soybeans etc. It refers to the specific type of crop that you are requesting to be used for your experimental or seed production workflows.  When filling out a capacity request, you will need to specify the crop in the designated field, which is essential for the planning and allocation of resources.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.cross_type
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Cross Type
dimensions.description: In crop science, cross type refers to the method of pollination and breeding used to produce new plant varieties.  It involves the intentional crossing of different plant lines or varieties to achieve specific traits or improvements in the offspring. Some of the values are Back Cross,Dev Cross, Self, Sibling Cross, Test Cross, Stack Cross

dimensions.name: capacity_request.cycle_time
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Cycle Time
dimensions.description: It is number of days that typically refers to the duration of a complete growth cycle of a plant from planting to harvest.  This term is essential for understanding the timing of agricultural practices and can vary significantly among different crops

dimensions.name: capacity_request.description
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Capacity Description
dimensions.description: This is the description that is captured on the capacity request upon creation in the Velocity application.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.disease_type
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Disease Type
dimensions.description: Refers to the classification of diseases that affect plants, typically based on their causal agents, symptoms, and the way they impact the crops. For example. COCHSA - Foot Rot, FUSASP - Fusarium spp., PYRNTE - Net blotch: barley, RAMUCC - Ramularia collo-cygni, RHYNSE - Leaf blotch: cereals, USTINH - Smut, loose: barley, COLLSP - Colletotrichum spp., FUSASP - Fusarium spp., MCPHSP - Macrophomina sp., PHYTMS - Phytophthora Root Rot, BIPOSP - Bipolaris sp,PENIOX - Root Rot, ALTEBA - Alternaria brassicae

dimensions.name: capacity_request.entries
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Entries
dimensions.description: The entries are the number of plots assigned to the capacity request. This is planned but actual value could change at the entryid or plot or field

dimensions.name: capacity_request.footprint
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Footprint
dimensions.description: The will provide the name that appears on the footprint

dimensions.name: capacity_request.harvest_type
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Harvest Type
dimensions.description: This refers to the method or technique used to gather crops from the field once they have reached maturity in the context of capacity requests It also shows the default harvest type of the track intent or the reps harvest type. For example Crop Yield Harvest, Hand - Yield, Yield Monitor, Seed Harvest,  Crop Destruct, Machine - Yield, Silage, Seed Yield Harvest, Crop Harvest, Veg Harvest, Cut Bags, Open Pollination

dimensions.name: capacity_request.induced_treatments
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Induced Treatments
dimensions.description: This refers to various methods used to create genetic variation or enhance specific traits in plants through controlled interventions.  These treatments can help breeders develop new varieties with desirable characteristics, such as improved yield, disease resistance, or environmental adaptability. For example Tar Spot, Goss's Bacterial Wilt, Fusarium Ear Rot, Nitrogen - Fall Applied, Spray - Off Label Requirements - Post, Disease - Charcoal Rot, Disease - Gibberella Stalk Rot (Gsr)

dimensions.name: capacity_request.manufacturing_trait_code
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Manufacturing Trait
dimensions.description: Manufacturing Trait Code is a 3 letter code used as an internal identifier for trait stacks associated with corn products. This value is also embedded in the pre commercial product name, and the manufacturing name of the hybrid.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.market
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayers market like WET, DRY, RM100,RM70, RM120

dimensions.name: capacity_request.maturity
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Maturity
dimensions.description: It is a value or a range which represents maturity of a plant in terms which are product-specific and which help determine optimal harvest. Average relative maturity of products in the experiment

dimensions.name: capacity_request.name
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Capacity Request Name
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request Name is a unique identifier that user enter for the specific project upon creation of capacity request  within the Capacity Request tab in the Velocity application. It is an unique name that you enter specifically for the capacity request itself.  The Request Name is used to identify the capacity request within the application and is required for submission. This can not be empty

dimensions.name: capacity_request.num_of_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the Bayer internal sites associated to the capacity request

dimensions.name: capacity_request.num_of_non_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Non Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the external sites associated to the capacity request.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.organization
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Organization
dimensions.description: This is the Business units like Enterprise, Breeding, Market Development, Production Research, IADT. It is also called as Requesting Organization

dimensions.name: capacity_request.originating_country
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Originating Country
dimensions.description: The term Originating Country typically refers to the country where a particular material or product is produced or sourced from. In the context of seed materials,  it indicates the country of origin for the seeds listed in the inventory or catalog.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.owner_groups
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group in the capacity request is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.owners
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.planting_year
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Planting Year
dimensions.description: This is the year when the plot or entryid will be planted. It is called Planting year of a plot or an entry

dimensions.name: capacity_request.plots_per_external_site
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Plots per external site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per external sites  typically refers to the allocation or distribution of plots that are designated for use at external locations or sites outside of the primary operational area. This likely refers to plots that are associated with external locations or farms that are not part of the internal organizational structure.  These could be sites that are managed externally or are part of a different operational framework.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.plots_per_internal_site
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Plots per internal site
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, plots per internal sites refers to the specific allocation of plots or growing areas designated within the internal sites for planting crops.  Each internal site can have multiple plots, and the Capacity Request helps in estimating and managing the number of plots needed based on the planned crop planting. This term usually pertains to plots that are managed or categorized within the internal framework of the application.  Internal sites may refer to subsites that are part of a larger site, focusing on specific areas or crops within that site.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.plots_per_site
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Plots per site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per sites refers to the specific allocation of planting areas (or plots) that are designated for use at various sites.  Each site can have multiple plots, and the capacity request helps in managing and organizing these plots based on the requirements for planting. This generally refers to the overall plots associated with a specific site, which can encompass multiple subsites.  It represents the totality of plots within a defined geographical area or farm.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.pollination_layout
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Pollination Layout
dimensions.description: It generally refers to the arrangement or strategy used for pollination in plant breeding.  This can include the selection of parent plants, the method of pollination (such as open, assisted, or controlled), and the tracking of reciprocal crosses.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.previous_crop
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Previous Crop
dimensions.description: This records the previous crop in the field

dimensions.name: capacity_request.project_ar
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Project AR
dimensions.description: In the context of a Capacity Request, the Project AR Name typically refers to a unique identifier used within a specific project or system,

dimensions.name: capacity_request.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.region
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Region
dimensions.description: Region name for the Bayer Site located in like United States of America(US), LAS, North America, Canada, EME,Africa,Asia,Brazil,LAN

dimensions.name: capacity_request.regional_hub
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Regional Hub
dimensions.description: Name of the hubs like Global, Africa, Asia, Europe, North America, South America, Latin America, Asia Pacific, Asia Africa, Middle East

dimensions.name: capacity_request.reps_per_site
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Reps per site
dimensions.description: The term reps_per_site in the context of the Capacity Request application typically refers to the number of replicates or copies of a specific entry that are associated with a site.  This concept is similar to how reps are used in experimental design, where a set of entries can have multiple replicates to ensure reliability and accuracy in data collection.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.requested_icb_male
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Requested ICB Male
dimensions.description: It is the Requested ICB Male information on the Capacity Request

dimensions.name: capacity_request.requester
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Requester
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, the requester is the individual who initiates the request for capacity

dimensions.name: capacity_request.rows_per_plot
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Rows per plot
dimensions.description: Rows per Plot refers to the number of rows that are designated for each plot within a planting session.  This metric is crucial for ensuring that the planting session is validated correctly, particularly in relation to the capacity request. When setting up a capacity request, it's important to ensure that the Rows per Plot aligns with the packet entry ratio, as discrepancies can lead to errors during validation.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.season
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Season
dimensions.description: This indicates the name of the growing season.It refers to a defined timeframe within which specific activities or operations are planned or executed Example Summer,Autumn, Winter, Spring, Winter in the country Brazil is called as Safrinha, Summer in the country Brazil is called as Verao

dimensions.name: capacity_request.specialty_requirements
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Speciality Requirements
dimensions.description: Specialty requirements refer to specific conditions or documentation that may be necessary for the request.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.status
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Status
dimensions.description: The indicates the current condition of a capacity request created in the Velocity table. For example Draft,  Pending Approval, Cancelled, Completed, Planning, Assigned, Exception Process, Deprioritized, Need More Data, Ready for Set Creation

dimensions.name: capacity_request.sub_market
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Sub Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayers market like ME1, RM5.1_5.4, ME4_DRY_EAST_ST

dimensions.name: capacity_request.submission_id
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Submission ID
dimensions.description: The submission ID on the capacity request is typically the unique identifier associated with a specific submission.  This ID is used to associate the capacity request with the protocol submission.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.submission_name
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Submission Name
dimensions.description: This provides name for the protocol submission

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_area
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Area
dimensions.description: The total area field in the Capacity Request workflow in Velocity is calculated based on information pulled from the footprint.  This data is essential for making full area calculations, which will be used in the Allocate Environment process.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_area_uom
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Area UOM
dimensions.description: The Unit Of Measure associated with Total Area

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_num_of_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_num_of_non_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Non Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Non-Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are not owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_plots
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Plots
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the total plots field is calculated based on the following formula: Total Plots = Seed Products * Reps/site * Non-Seed product treatments + border plots. This calculation helps determine the number of plots required for your request based on the specified parameters.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_short_row_equivalent
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Short Row Equivalent
dimensions.description: A unit for estimation of seed production

dimensions.name: capacity_request.total_sq_ft
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Sq Ft
dimensions.description: The total square footage area in the Capacity Request is calculated based on the selections made in the required fields across all sections, including the Inputs Tab.  This area is automatically computed and displayed in the Flats Total Area and Pots or Flats Total Area fields.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.trait_stack_abbreviation
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Trait Stack Abbr.
dimensions.description: Shortened name of the trait stack. For example BR2, FSR, BLSB, ASR1,DER, FER, GLS, CONV etc

dimensions.name: capacity_request.trial_intent
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Trail Intent
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the Trial Intent refers to the description of the purpose of the trial being conducted.  This field allows users to specify the objective or goal of their experimental or seed production workflows.

dimensions.name: capacity_request.trial_type
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Trail Type
dimensions.description: It is an experiment trial type. For example Research Trial, Field Trial, Observation, Commercial Trial - Market Development, Nursery, Field Trial - Seed Treatment, Seed Production, Yield Trial, Commercial Trial, Tech Dev / Research Trial, Performance - Validation, Performance - Adaptability, Commercial Trial - Third Party, Commercial Trial - University, Agronomy / Commercial Trial, Value-Added, Recommendation, Commercial Trial - Competitor Plot, Commercial Trial - Side by Side, Market Dev / Research Trial, Commercial Trial - FTN and/or Field Scale Spatial

dimensions.name: capacity_request.num_plants
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Total Plants
dimensions.description: The number of plants for the capacity request

dimensions.name: capacity_request.non_seed_product_treatments
dimensions.title: Capacity Request Non Seed Product Treatments
dimensions.description: This captures the number of product treaments that are not related to seed

dimensions.name: environments.rtdl_territory
dimensions.title: Environments Environment RTDL Territory
dimensions.description: It gives information about RTDL Territory recorded at the environment level for each capacity request

dimensions.name: environments.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Environments Capacity Request Id
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each capacity request made within the Capacity Request workflow in the Velocity application This ID helps users track and manage their requests effectively throughout the process.

measures.name: climatological_normal.avg_of_min_temperature
measures.title: Climatological Normal Average Minimum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest temperature recorded during the day. Also called Min Temp, Daily Low Temp, Lowest Temperature.

measures.name: climatological_normal.avg_of_max_temperature
measures.title: Climatological Normal Average Maximum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest temperature recorded during the day. Also called Max Temp, Daily High Temp, Peak Temperature.

measures.name: climatological_normal.avg_of_min_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Climatological Normal Average Minimum Dew Point Temperature

cubes.name: entry_answers
cubes.title: Entry Answers
cubes.description: Field answers serves as a single source of truth for aggregating data from various systems within the organization.  It plays a crucial role in ensuring that Data Q and A system has accurate and consolidated information, which is essential for effective data management and analysis. It shows answers, labeled according to the type of answers being collected.  It contains velocity field answers at an set entry level i.e entryid level. It only contains answer values for the entryid that exists in the either in Experiment Set Entries or Line Advancement Plan Entries It does hold any answer history of for a given Entry ID,Instance Sequence, Question Code but only the latest answer value.

cubes.name: experiment_sets_entries
cubes.title: Experiment Sets Entries
cubes.description: Field set entries are sub-units of a set in the Velocity application. Each entry can have its own specific instructions that are distinct from other parts of the set.  These entries are associated with different geospatial areas in the field (or containers in a greenhouse) where specific materials are intended to be planted. In an experimental set, there may be numerous entries connected to individual plots, while in a production set, there might be fewer entries depending on the recipe required for a product.  Each entry conveys to the grower and the tools they use what material should be planted where, along with all the relevant instructions.

measures.name: experiment_sets_entries.count_distinct_entryid
measures.title: Experiment Sets Entries Distinct count of Entry ID
measures.description: This is the distinct count of the EntryID's from the Experiment Set Entries

measures.name: experiment_sets_entries.count_distinct_of_experiment_id
measures.title: Experiment Sets Entries  Count of Experiments
measures.description: This is to get the count of experiment ID in the capacity request.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.entryid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an experiment set entry in the Velocity application.  An Experiment set entry id is created only upon creation of a capacity request. An Experiment set entry id is also called as Entry ID. Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.setid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.access_grower_groups
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Access Grower Groups

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Capacity Request ID

dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Protocol Name
dimensions.description: It is the name of the protocol

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.protocolid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Protocol ID
dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.access_usergroups
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Access user Groups
dimensions.description: User Groups are defined by business and consist of users from similar roles, squads, or units.  They enable visibility, sharing, and editing of trials among squad and unit members, facilitating collaboration and accountability

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.access_growergroups

dimensions.description: Type of analysis model used

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.block_id

dimensions.description: Experiments unique identifier. Represents test_set_id in Midas

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.block_name
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Block Name
dimensions.description: A non-unique string used to identify the experimental set. Represents test set name for records from FTS.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.catalog_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Catalog ID
dimensions.description: A Catalog ID is a unique identifier generated by the Velocity system for a specific catalog record.  It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.catalog_seed_type
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Catalog Seed Type
dimensions.description: The seed type of the catalog. For example Internal Seed, Commercial Check

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.constructs
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Constructs
dimensions.description: This field contains the identities of the constructs used in the transformation process, provided the germplasm contains any transgenic events,

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.controltypes_coded
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Control Types Codes

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.deactivationreason_coded
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Entry Deactivation Reason Code
dimensions.description: A deactivation reason is a justification provided by the user when they deactivate plot or entry.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.entry_number
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Entry Number
dimensions.description: The entrys order in the layout. This number is used to uniquely identify entries within a set. It is unique only within the scope of that specific set and is assigned sequentially starting from 1 up to the total number of entries in the set.  Generic entry numbers do not have any inherent business meaning or guaranteed relation to other identifiers

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.entry_sequence_number
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Entry Sequence Number
dimensions.description: It is sequence order of Entry IDs in the layout .This number describes the order in which an entry should be placed in its layout. It is determined based on instructions from randomization (for trial sets) or by the nursery row pattern service (for production sets).  The sequence number indicates the placement direction and helps in constructing the layout on a map

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.experiment_name
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Experiment Name
dimensions.description: An experiment name refers to the specific title or identifier given to a particular experiment.  This name helps in organizing and referencing the experiment within the system. It is part of the structured design that allows users to gather and analyze data effectively.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.fts_germplasmid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries FTS Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier from FTS application

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.velmat_material_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Velocity Material ID
dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.geneticmaterialid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: This captures midas genetic material id

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.germplasmid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.is_transgenic

dimensions.description: Flag indicating if the germplasm contains a transgenic event

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.transgenic_events
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Transgenic Events
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new speciemen through a vector

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.iscontrol
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Is Control
dimensions.description: Flag to indicate the controltypes. True means controltype exis

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.linecode

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.linetype
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Line Type
dimensions.description: It is legacy piece of data that can be HYBRID, FINISHED, CODED, or SEGPOP.  This typically refers to the specific genetic lines being used in the breeding process. Different line types may have distinct genetic backgrounds and traits.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.material_fulfillment_groups

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.p360_product_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries p360 Product ID
dimensions.description: Describes the product 360 product identifier for velocity experiments. If the plants in the experiment are associated to a product intended to sell, this field will have values

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.pedigree
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Pedigree
dimensions.description: Pedigree refers to a concatenated value that includes components such as Origin, Lineage or Line Code, and Precommercial name. It is string version of parental ancestry

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.populationid
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Population ID
dimensions.description: a Population ID refers to a unique identifier assigned to a specific Population. This ID helps in managing and tracking the associated data of that Population

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.relativematurity
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.rep
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Repition
dimensions.description: It indicates how many times a specific activity or set of entries is performed or recorded

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.population_name
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Population Name
dimensions.description: A population name refers to the designation given to a group of germplasm that is created during the breeding process.  Specifically, it is used to identify the progeny in the Material Marketplace, where users can see details such as the Population Name, Male Parent, and Female Parent data fields.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.set_created_date
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Set Creation Date
dimensions.description: It is date of set creation. Returns a stringified date in UTC format.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.germplasm_group_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Germplasm Group ID
dimensions.description: It is a group associated to this germplasm.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.experiment_design
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Experiment Design
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.product_type
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Product Type
dimensions.description: It is Material category like lot, seed, inventory, catalog etc

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.set_type
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Set Type
dimensions.description: It is an name given to make it more readable. Example values are Simple, Trial, Production

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.material_type
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Material Type
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.source_str
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Source String
dimensions.description: The Test Set name corresponding to when the genetic material was produced.source_str from midas for a genetic material, business logic stored in text box based on linecode of parents

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.sets_material_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Inventory ID
dimensions.description: An inventory ID is typically a unique identifier assigned to a specific inventory item within a system like MIDAS. It helps in tracking and managing inventory accurately.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.set_name
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Set Name
dimensions.description: A set name refers to the title given to a planned planting or grow out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.sets_material_name
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Set Material Name
dimensions.description: It is material name of the set. a material name typically refers to the name associated with a specific material that used in the set. This could be linked to the Material ID, which is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material, such as an inventory barcode, lot ID, or catalog item ID.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.treatmentnumber
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Treatment Number
dimensions.description: It is a treatment number. A treatment number is a unique identifier used to identify all treatment lines that are components of one treatment in the context of chemical applications. In the Velocity system, treatment numbers must start at 1 and follow a continuous sequence (e.g., 1, 2, 3, 4).  This numbering is important for organizing and managing treatments effectively.

dimensions.name: experiment_sets_entries.treatment_id
dimensions.title: Experiment Sets Entries Treatment ID
dimensions.description: It is list of Seed Treatment Applications. A Treatment ID is the globally unique identifier for a Velocity experimental treatment.

cubes.name: gin_cotton_data
cubes.title: Gin Cotton
cubes.description: This cube helps to store cotton gin data used in downstream operations such as fiber quality testing (HVI testing), calculating yield and predicted LP. Cotton ginning sample data processed using GSP (Ginning Support Program) desktop application.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.scw
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Seed Cotton Weight(SCW)
dimensions.description: This is the Seed Cotton Weight observation for the cotton boll sample.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.scw_uom
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton SCW UOM
dimensions.description: Is the Seed Cotton Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.lint
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Lint
dimensions.description: This is the Lint Weight observation when delinted.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.lint_uom
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Lint UOM
dimensions.description: This is the Lint Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.fsw
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Fuzzy Seed Weight(FSW)
dimensions.description: This the Fuzzy Seed Weight observation when delinted.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.fsw_uom
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton FSW UOM
dimensions.description: This is the Fuzzy Seed Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.lp
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Lint Percent
dimensions.description: Is the Lint Percent of the cotton sample. Calculated as follows: LINT/(LINT+FSW)

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.turn_out
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Turn Out
dimensions.description: This is the Lint/SCW percent

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.gin
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton GIN
dimensions.description: This is the computer name used during cotton processing in Ginning Support Program(GSP) Desktop app.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.bsw
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Black Seed Weight
dimensions.description: This is the Black Seed Weight observation.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.bsw_uom
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton BSW UOM
dimensions.description: Black Seed Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.box
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Box ID
dimensions.description: This is the Box ID label used to group the cotton samples for the HVI system.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.bolp
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Bolls Per Plant(BOLP)
dimensions.description: Bolls per plant observation.

dimensions.name: gin_cotton_data.gin_date
dimensions.title: Gin Cotton Gin Date
dimensions.description: This is the date and time the sample was last processed.

cubes.name: lab_observations
cubes.title: Lab Observations
cubes.description: lab_observations

dimensions.name: lab_observations.entry_id
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Entry ID
dimensions.description: The unique identifier for each entry.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.observation_name
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Observation Name
dimensions.description: Refers to the specific title or label assigned to a particular observation

dimensions.name: lab_observations.question_code
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Question Code
dimensions.description: Question Code refers to a unique string used to identify a specific question, serving as the primary key for that question within the system

dimensions.name: lab_observations.attribute
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Attribute
dimensions.description: Attribute refers to a specific characteristic or property associated with the data collected during experiments.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.instance_seq
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Instance Sequence
dimensions.description: Instance Sequence refers to the specific order or arrangement of individual instances of data collected during an experiment or observation

dimensions.name: lab_observations.is_deactivated_dsr
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Is Deactivated DSR
dimensions.description: Is Deactivated DSR refers to a flag indicating whether a specific observation has been marked as deactivated due to the application of Deleted Studentized Residuals (DSR) calculations.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.is_deactivated_qaqc
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Is Deactivated QAQC
dimensions.description: Is Deactivated QAQC refers to a flag indicating whether a specific observation has been marked as deactivated due to Quality Assurance and Quality Control (QAQC) processes.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.observable
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Observable
dimensions.description: Observable refers to a specific measurement or data point that can be recorded during an experiment or analysis.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.observation_time
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Observation Time
dimensions.description: Observation Time refers to the specific time at which a measurement or data point is recorded, it is crucial for tracking when observations were made, which can impact the interpretation of results.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.reason_dsr
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Reason DSR
dimensions.description: Reason DSR refers to the justification for using Deleted Studentized Residuals (DSR) to identify and flag outlier data points, ensuring the integrity of the analysis.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.reason_qaqc
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Reason QAQC
dimensions.description: Reason QAQC

dimensions.name: lab_observations.sample
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Sample
dimensions.description: Sample refers to a subset of data or observations selected from a larger population for analysis or experimentation.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.uom_code
dimensions.title: Lab Observations UOM Code
dimensions.description: UOM Code is a shorthand for 'Unit of Measure' code, which specifies the measurement units for data collected in lab tests, ensuring consistent interpretation and analysis.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.value
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Value
dimensions.description: Value refers to the specific measurement or data point recorded during an experiment or observation.

dimensions.name: lab_observations.value_type
dimensions.title: Lab Observations Value Type
dimensions.description: Value Type refers to the classification of the data input for a specific measurement or observation. It determines how the data can be entered or utilized within the system.

cubes.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries
cubes.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries
cubes.description: The Line Advancement Plan (LAP) is a structured approach used within the application to facilitate the advancement of product lines.  It encompasses various methodologies, selection methods, and approval processes to ensure effective management and progression of product lines. It stores information for the Entry ID's that are of the set type as production

measures.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.count_distinct_entry_id
measures.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Distinct count of Entry ID
measures.description: This is the distinct count of the EntryID's from the Experiment Set Entries

measures.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.count_distinct_of_experiment_id
measures.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries  Count of Experiments
measures.description: This is to get the count of experiment ID in the capacity request.

measures.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.count_distinct_capacity_request_id
measures.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Distinct count of Capacity Request ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Capacity Request ID recorded in the velocity application
measures.shortTitle: Distinct count of Capacity Request ID

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of a capacity request in the Velocity application

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.entry_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an experiment set entry in the Velocity application.  An Experiment set entry id is created only upon creation of a capacity request. An Experiment set entry id is also called as Entry ID. Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.line_advancement_plan_name
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Line Advancement Plan Name
dimensions.description: The Line Advancement Plan (LAP) does have a designated name

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.line_advancement_plan_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Line Advancement Plan ID
dimensions.description: The Line Advancement Plan (LAP) does have an ID. IT is system generated unique identifier

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.set_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.protocol_name
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Protocol Name
dimensions.description: It is the name of the protocol

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.protocol_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Protocol ID
dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.access_usergroups
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Access user Groups
dimensions.description: User Groups are defined by business and consist of users from similar roles, squads, or units.  They enable visibility, sharing, and editing of trials among squad and unit members, facilitating collaboration and accountability

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.access_growergroups
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Access Grower Groups
dimensions.description: This provides the information about the growers groups associated to the record

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.catalog_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Catalog ID
dimensions.description: A Catalog ID is a unique identifier generated by the Velocity system for a specific catalog record.  It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.catalog_seed_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Catalog Seed Type
dimensions.description: The seed type of the catalog. For example Internal Seed, Commercial Check

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.constructs
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Constructs
dimensions.description: This field contains the identities of the constructs used in the transformation process, provided the germplasm contains any transgenic events,

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.entry_number
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Entry Number
dimensions.description: The entrys order in the layout. This number is used to uniquely identify entries within a set. It is unique only within the scope of that specific set and is assigned sequentially starting from 1 up to the total number of entries in the set.  Generic entry numbers do not have any inherent business meaning or guaranteed relation to other identifiers

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.entry_sequence_number
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Entry Sequence Number
dimensions.description: It is sequence order of Entry IDs in the layout .This number describes the order in which an entry should be placed in its layout. It is determined based on instructions from randomization (for trial sets) or by the nursery row pattern service (for production sets).  The sequence number indicates the placement direction and helps in constructing the layout on a map

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.fts_germplasmid
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries FTS Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier from FTS application

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.velmat_material_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Velocity Material ID
dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.genetic_material_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: This captures midas genetic material id

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.germplasm_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.is_transgenic
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Is Trangenic
dimensions.description: Flag indicating if the germplasm contains a transgenic event

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.transgenic_events
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Transgenic Events
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new speciemen through a vector

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.line_code
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Line Code
dimensions.description: It is an user defined name applied to a given germplasm

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.line_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Line Type
dimensions.description: It is legacy piece of data that can be HYBRID, FINISHED, CODED, or SEGPOP.  This typically refers to the specific genetic lines being used in the breeding process. Different line types may have distinct genetic backgrounds and traits.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.material_fulfillment_groups
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Material Fullfillment Groups
dimensions.description: Material fulfillment groups in the Line Advancement Plan set entries are designated user groups responsible for managing physical inventory and fulfilling material requests within the materials marketplace.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.no_of_plots_assigned
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Plots Assigned
dimensions.description: The count of entries associated with the set. Unless a set is assigned to a field or plot or entryid, this will be null

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.origin
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Origin
dimensions.description: The Origin in the Line Advancement Plan set entries refers to the specific source or lineage of materials, which are essential for tracking material development.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.p360_product_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries p360 Product ID
dimensions.description: Describes the product 360 product identifier for velocity experiments. If the plants in the experiment are associated to a product intended to sell, this field will have values

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.pedigree
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Pedigree
dimensions.description: Pedigree refers to a concatenated value that includes components such as Origin, Lineage or Line Code, and Precommercial name. It is string version of parental ancestry

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.population_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Population ID
dimensions.description: a Population ID refers to a unique identifier assigned to a specific Population. This ID helps in managing and tracking the associated data of that Population

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.relative_maturity
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.population_name
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Population Name
dimensions.description: A population name refers to the designation given to a group of germplasm that is created during the breeding process. dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.set_name

Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.sets_material_name

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_set_entries.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Set Entries Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

cubes.name: line_adv_plan_sets_geography

cubes.description: Set geography allows users to manage and organize their planting or growing activities based on specific locations.  This is particularly important in agricultural and controlled environment settings where different areas may have varying conditions, resources, or requirements.  By filtering and managing sets by location, users can ensure that they are optimizing their planting strategies and resources effectively. It helps users to focus on the specific geographic areas they are working with, leading to better planning and execution of their agricultural practices. It stores information for the Entry ID's that are part of Line Advancement Plan Set Entries or Nursery Operations

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_sets_geography.planter_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Sets Geography Planter Type
dimensions.description: The typical values for planter type include options such as Packet, Cassette, and Cassette (w Bottle). It refers to the specific category of planting equipment being used. When creating or editing a planting session, users can select from different planter types,  which include:  Packet: This option does not require a planter mode. Cassette: This option allows for the selection of a planter mode. Cassette (w Bottle): Similar to the Cassette option, but includes the use of bottles.

dimensions.name: line_adv_plan_sets_geography.planter_mode

dimensions.description: The Planter Mode refers to the specific settings that determine how planting sessions are configured based on the type of planter selected. When users choose a planter type, such as Cassette or Cassette (w Bottle), they will see a dropdown box for Planter Mode with various options, including Single Cell Plot (Uniform Plot Length), Single Cell Plot (Non-Uniform Plot Length), Multi Cell Plot, Strip Trial

cubes.name: line_advancement_plan

cubes.description: line advancement plan

measures.title: Line Advancement Plan Miniumn Keep Quantity
measures.description: This gives us the minimum keep quantity

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.entry_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an experiment set entry in the Velocity application.  An Experiment set entry id is created only upon creation of a capacity request. An Experiment set entry id is also called as Entry ID. Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.is_template
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Is Template
dimensions.description: This tells is the LAP is generated using the template. True means yes it is generated using template. False means no is it not generated through use of template

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.lap_owners
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan LAP Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Line Advancement Application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.lap_owner_groups
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan LAP Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group at the LAP level is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.pollination_parent_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Pollination Parent Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of parent used in the pollination process.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.progeny_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Progeny Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of progeny.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.created_by_user
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Created By User
dimensions.description: The Created By User in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the individual or system account that initiated the creation of a specific entry within the plan.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.created_date
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Created Date
dimensions.description: The Created Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was first created, providing a timeline for tracking the addition of data within the system.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.modified_by_user
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Modified By User
dimensions.description: The Modified By User in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the individual or system account responsible for the most recent changes made to an entry, ensuring accountability in data management.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.modified_date
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Modified Date
dimensions.description: The Modified Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was last updated or changed.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.pollination_event_status
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Pollination Event Status
dimensions.description: The pollination event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a pollination event, helping to track its progress from creation to completion.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.harvest_event_status
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Harvest Event Status
dimensions.description: The harvest event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a harvest event, helping to track its progress from initiation to completion.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.pollination_intentid
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Pollination Intent ID
dimensions.description: The pollination intent id in the Line Advancement Plan serves as a unique identifier for tracking and managing specific pollination activities associated with each entry.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.progeny
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Progeny
dimensions.description: The progeny in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the offspring generated from specific breeding activities, which are tracked and managed within the plan to assess their development and characteristics.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.male_parent
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Male Parent
dimensions.description: The male parent refers to the male entity used in breeding activities, which contributes genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.female_parent
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Female Parent
dimensions.description: The female parent refers to the female entity used in breeding activities, which provides genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.is_placeholder
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Is Placeholder
dimensions.description: This indicates whether the entry is a placeholder.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.anticipated_pollination_attempts
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Anticipated Pollination Attempts
dimensions.description: The Anticipated Pollination Attempts refers to the number of times you plan to pollinate each plant or set entry to achieve your desired harvest target quantity.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.harvest_target_quantity
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Harvest Target Quantity
dimensions.description: The harvest target quantity refers to the specific amount of plant material or flowers that you aim to collect from a breeding plan during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.harvest_target_quantity_uom_uode
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Harvest Target Quantity UOM
dimensions.description: The Harvest Target Quantity UOM refers to the unit of measurement used to specify the desired amount of plant material or flowers you aim to collect during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.harvest_method
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Harvest Method
dimensions.description: The Harvest Method refers to the various approaches for collecting plants during the harvest phase, which include Bulk, Select, Select & Bulk and Bulk Group.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.harvest_selections
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Harvest Selections
dimensions.description: Harvest Selections refers to the number of individual plants or entries that you plan to select for harvesting based on specific criteria.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.blocks
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Blocks
dimensions.description: Blocks are used to separate intents and create multiple sets, allowing for organized management of harvesting plans.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.block_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Block ID
dimensions.description: Block ID is a unique identifier for each block, facilitating effective management and referencing of specific blocks within the application.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.reciprocal_of_intent_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Reciprocal of Intent ID
dimensions.description: The Reciprocal of Intent ID is a unique identifier for tracking reciprocal pollination events between two plants, facilitating effective management of these intents within the application.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.male_block
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Male Block
dimensions.description: The Male Block is a designated section for organizing and managing male plant intents, ensuring effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.male_block_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Male Block ID
dimensions.description: The Male Block ID is a unique identifier for a specific block that organizes and manages male plant intents, facilitating effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.male_set_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Male Set ID
dimensions.description: The Male Set ID is a unique identifier for a specific set that organizes and manages male plant intents, essential for tracking male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.planting_cross_instrn_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Planting Cross Instruction ID
dimensions.description: Planting Cross Instruction ID is a unique identifier that outlines the guidelines for planting crosses

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.lap_cross_type
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan LAP Cross Type
dimensions.description: The LAP Cross Type refers to the specific category of cross used in breeding, including Self, Test, and Development crosses, which guide the breeding strategy and management of plant breeding activities.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.reciprocal_cross
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Reciprocal Cross
dimensions.description: Determines if the PCI will have reciprocal crosses

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.pollination_operations
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Pollination Operations
dimensions.description: Determines pollination operation of the PCI

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.cross_type_pattern
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Cross Type Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the cross type pattern of the PCI

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.icb
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan ICB
dimensions.description: Determines if PCI supports multiple, different male parents within a block

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.custom_row_pattern
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Custom Row Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the gender layout of a custom pattern

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.custom_pattern_pairing
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Custom Pattern Pairing
dimensions.description: Determines which entries correspond with each other

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.prcsg_intent_id
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Processing Intent ID
dimensions.description: The Processing Intent ID is a unique identifier used to track and manage processing activities related to specific breeding intents.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.keep_quantity_min
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Keep Quantity Min
dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity Min is the minimum amount of seeds or materials that must be retained for each breeding intent to ensure sufficient availability for processing or evaluation.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.keep_quantity_max
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Keep Quantity Max

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.keep_quantity_uom_code
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Keep Quantity UOM
dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity UOM code in the Line Advancement Plan specifies the unit of measure used for quantifying the seeds or materials retained for each breeding intent.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.treatment_ids
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Treatment ID
dimensions.description: The treatment IDs are unique identifiers assigned to specific treatments or breeding intents within the plan.

dimensions.name: line_advancement_plan.unprocessed_inventory_count
dimensions.title: Line Advancement Plan Unprocessed Inventory
dimensions.description: The unprocessed inventory count is the number of inventories that have not yet been processed

cubes.name: mactracker_nsp
cubes.title: Mactracker NSP
cubes.description: This table contains information about the NSP (Nursery Seed Packing) tracking data. It includes details such as batch packet barcode, batch source barcode, machine location, machine serial number, batch type, machine MAC address, batch count, and the number of packets in the batch.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_batch_packet_barcode
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Batch Packet Barcode
dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_batch_source_barcode
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Batch Source Barcode
dimensions.description: Alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barcode applied to the plot corresponding to when the genetic material was produced. It is displayed as 'I00879540871575711010000'.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_machine_location
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Machine Location
dimensions.description: This is the location of the machine. Is a character entity of fixed length, with an upper limit of 3 characters. It is an indicator of where the batch was processed. (3 letter code of physical machine location). It is displayed as a 3 character code from the mactracker_location_lookup table for valid values.  It is generated from the shellmatic application.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_machine_serial
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Machine Serial
dimensions.description: This is the serial of the machine.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_batch_type
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Batch Type
dimensions.description: Is a character entity of variable length, with an upper limit of 255 number of characters. It is displayed as a character string. It is not used as a primary key OR a foreign key. This is 'NSP' for all rows as the machine type is mactracker_NSP.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_machine_mac_address
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Machine MAC Address
dimensions.description: This is the MAC address of the machine.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_batch_count
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Batch Count
dimensions.description: Is an integer ranging from 0-999999999. This number represents a numeric value based on the actual count for the batch. It is displayed as '6'.

dimensions.name: mactracker_nsp.nsp_batch_num_of_packets
dimensions.title: Mactracker NSP NSP Packets in Batch
dimensions.description: It is the number of packets in the source batch. It is an instruction or parameter given to the process. It takes values from 1-5 and is fixed for the batch, if the batch is getting split into 3, all the packets will have the same value.

cubes.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3
cubes.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3
cubes.description: This table contains information about the shellmatic 3 machine processing batches. It includes details such as machine location, serial number, type, processing start and finish times, source set, operator, recipe used, target settings, size distributions, color averages, rejection percentages, crop type, weight, seed counts (accepted and presorted), treatment details (ID, name, pump volume, dry time, pump speed, volume per revolution, treatment rate), and other relevant attributes related to the seed processing operation.

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.sum_of_seed_count
measures.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Total Accepted Seed Count
measures.description: Total quantity of seed accepted after sorting

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.sum_of_count_presorted
