measures.description: This is total quantity of seeds presorted

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.sum_of_unaccepted_seed_count
measures.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Total Unaccepted Seed Count
measures.description: This is total quantity of seeds not accepted after sorting

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.count_distinct_of_src_plot_bid
measures.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Total Packet
measures.description: This is the count of distinct source plot barcode for a given set of records

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.min_of_datetime_start
measures.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 First Processing Start Datetime
measures.description: This is the First Processing Finish Datetime for a given set of records

measures.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.max_of_datetime_finish

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.src_plot_bid
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Plot Barcode
dimensions.description: It is formatted as a string starting with 'P' followed by 23 integers. An example is 'P00000000879548099137769'. It is generated in Enterprise data systems from SPI (seed processing instruction) API.  It is a barcode applied to the plot corresponding to when the genetic material was produced. It is called as Source Plot Bid or Source Plot Barcode

dimensions.description: This is the location of the machine. Is a character entity of fixed length, with an upper limit of 3 characters. It is an indicator of where the batch was processed. (3 letter code of physical machine location). It is displayed as a 3 character code from the mactracker_location_lookup table for valid values.  It is generated from the shellmatic application. It is not empty

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treatment_name

dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length alphabets and special characters, with an upper limit of 255 characters. dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treater_pump_volume
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Treatment Pump Volume
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment applied to the batch in mL.  It is generated from the shellmatic 3 PC application. It is displayed as '21.9384' It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treater_dry_time
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Treatment Dry Time
dimensions.description: Is a variable length field storing an integer value. It represents the amount of time in seconds the batch is allowed to dry. It is displayed as '80'. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treater_pump_speed
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Treatment Pump Seed
dimensions.description: Is a floating point value that represents the RPM setting of the treater pump used for the batch.  It is generated from the settings file of the application. It is displayed as '150'.

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treater_pump_vol_per_rev
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Volume Per Revolution
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment delivered with each revolution of the pump in mL.  Treater pump volume per revolution is generated from the settings file of the shelmatic and can be calibrated by the application. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: mactracker_shellmatic_3.treater_treatment_rate
dimensions.title: Mactracker Shellmatic 3 Treatment Rate
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment to be applied per 1000 seeds.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It is displayed as '0.0. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

cubes.name: mactracker_ytp
cubes.title: MACTRACKER YTP
cubes.description: The mactracker_ytp cube contains information about the batches processed by the YTP machines.  Each record in this cube represents a batch of genetic material that has been processed by a YTP machine,  including details such as the batch packet barcode, source barcode, machine location, machine serial number, batch type, machine MAC address, batch count, and the number of packets in the batch. This data is crucial for tracking and managing the distribution of genetic material in breeding operations.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.batch_packet_barcode
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Batch Packet Barcode
dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.batch_source_barcode
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Batch Source Barcode
dimensions.description: Alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barcode applied to the plot corresponding to when the genetic material was produced. It is displayed as 'I00879540871575711010000'.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.machine_location
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Machine Location
dimensions.description: This is the location of the machine. Is a character entity of fixed length, with an upper limit of 3 characters. It is an indicator of where the batch was processed. (3 letter code of physical machine location). It is displayed as a 3 character code from the mactracker_location_lookup table for valid values. It is generated from the shellmatic application. It is not empty

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.machine_serial
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Machine Serial
dimensions.description: This is the serial of the machine.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.batch_type
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Batch Type
dimensions.description: This is the type of the batch.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.machine_mac_address
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Machine MAC Address
dimensions.description: This is the MAC address of the machine.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.batch_count
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Batch Count
dimensions.description: Is an integer ranging from 0-999999999. This number represents a numeric value based on the actual count for the batch. It is displayed as '6'.

dimensions.name: mactracker_ytp.batch_num_of_packets
dimensions.title: MACTRACKER YTP Packets in Batch
dimensions.description: It is the number of packets in the source batch. It is an instruction or parameter given to the process. It takes values from 1-5 and is fixed for the batch, if the batch is getting split into 3, all the packets will have the same value.

cubes.description: Contains detailed information about experimental entries in breeding trials, including plot details, germplasm information, and experimental design specifics.

measures.name: ops_experiment_entries.count_ops_experiment_entries
measures.title: OPS Experiment Entries Count of OPS Experiment Entries
measures.description: The total number of OPS Experiment Entries

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot ID
dimensions.description: The unique identifier for a plot(typically midas_plot_id) within the Field Testing Suite (FTS).

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.absolute_column
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Absolute Column
dimensions.description: The absolute Y coordinate of a Plot within a Field independent of the repetitions

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.absolute_range
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Absolute Range
dimensions.description: The absolute X coordinate of a Plot within a Field independent of the repetitions

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.barcode
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Barcode
dimensions.description: The barcode applied to the response inventory within the R&D pipeline.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.block_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Block ID
dimensions.description: Experiment's unique identifier. Represents test_set_id in Midas

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.block_name
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Block Name
dimensions.description: A non-unique string used to identify the experimental set. Represents test set name for records from FTS.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: Unique identifier from the capacity request velocity application. An individual capacity request describes a forecast for the space needed to conduct the experiment.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.check_type
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Check Type
dimensions.description: If the entry is a control, this is a categorization of that control. Examples are market leader, best internal variety, etc

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.columns_wide
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Columns Wide
dimensions.description: The default number of columns (i.e., vertical columns) to plant for a Repetition

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.constructs
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Constructs
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.country
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Country
dimensions.description: Defines the country in which the location resides.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.crop
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Crop
dimensions.description: The crop under test in the experiment.The unique identifier representing the names of current veg crops of Bayer Crop Science. It is defined as it appears in Enterprise (MIDAS) reference data tables.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.detection_success_rate_reviewed
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Detection Success Rate Reviewed
dimensions.description: Flag specifying that the observations taken from the repetition have gone through outlier analysis

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_design
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment Design
dimensions.description: A randomization pattern planned for, or applied, to a Repetition in a Field

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment ID
dimensions.description: Unique identifier of the experiment. An experiment is usually conducted by planting a variety multiple times to study how different variables impact it. Variables can include location, treatments, agricultural processes etc.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_name
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment Name
dimensions.description: User entered name for the experiment

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_stage_cd
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment Stage Code
dimensions.description: Abbreviation for the experimental stage (e.g, S1, P4)

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_stage_name
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment Stage Name
dimensions.description: Identifies a stage in the pipeline in which the experiment is being conducted (e.g., Screening 1, Pre-Commercial 4)

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.experiment_type_name
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Experiment Type Name
dimensions.description: Purpose of the experiment as identified by the pipeline function (e.g., Research, Technology Development, Government, Licensed, Regulatory)

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_geometry
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field Geometry
dimensions.description: GeoJSON Feature for a BR_FIELD_ID(midas_field_id) as returned by the location360 web service

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field ID
dimensions.description: The unique identifiers for this Field resource

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_latitude

dimensions.description: The latitude of a point in the field location

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_length
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field Length
dimensions.description: The length of the field in meters

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_longitude
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field Longitude
dimensions.description: The longitude of a point in the field location

dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field Name
dimensions.description: Describing areas of land that can be used for growing crops.The textual name of this field as it was defined in MIDAS NOTE: this element is not guaranteed to be unique across multiple fields

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.field_width
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Field Width
dimensions.description: The width of the field

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.fts_inventory_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries FTS Inventory ID
dimensions.description: An identifier from a legacy system (typically MIDAS) to represent this inventory

dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: The official Source that describes when, where and by whom genetic material was produced.source_str from midas for a genetic material, business logic stored in text box based on linecode of parents

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.germplasm_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The unique identifier from a legacy system (typically MIDAS) to represent this germplasm

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.grow_month
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Grow Month
dimensions.description: A numeric value indicating month, interpreted differently by different pipeline functions. Example:01,04

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.grower
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Grower
dimensions.description: Identifies the party responsible for growing the material for the experiment

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.harvest_date
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Harvest Date
dimensions.description: Date on which which the field was harvested,

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.harvest_type
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Harvest Type
dimensions.description: Identifies how the repetition was harvested(e.g., Grain, Silage, Lint, Fruit)

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.harvested_plot_length
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Harvested Plot Length
dimensions.description: Length of the material harvested out of the plot in meters

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.harvested_plot_width
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Harvested Plot Width
dimensions.description: Width of the material harvested out of the plot in meters

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.harvested_rows_plot
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Harvested Rows Plot
dimensions.description: Straight lines of plants harvested across a dimension of the field.When plot.harvested_rows is null then rep.track_harvest_rows_per_plot

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.inventory_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Inventory ID
dimensions.description: This field representing name inventories/ksuid.An Inventory represents an available seed. It is linked to a germplasm.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_acknowledged
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Acknowledged
dimensions.description: Flag specifying whether or not the repetition has been acknowledged for receipt by grower program

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_check
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Check
dimensions.description: If this is true indicates that the entry is a Performance check (i.e., control).

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_final
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Final
dimensions.description: Flag specifying that QA/QC has been completed by the owner

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_irrigated
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Irrigated
dimensions.description: Indicates if a field has been irrigated

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_mapped
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Mapped
dimensions.description: Flag specifying when the repetition has been put in the field logically, not actually

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_plot_deactivated
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Plot Deactivated
dimensions.description: Flag for specifying if the plot is deactivated

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_rejected
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Rejected
dimensions.description: Flag specifying that the repetition should not be used by downstream applications

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_relinquished
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Relinquished
dimensions.description: Flag specifying that the grower has captured all observations

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.is_transgenic
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Is Transgenic
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new specimen through a vector

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.line_code
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Line Code
dimensions.description: Indicates that this germplasm has transgentic events

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.line_type
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Line Type
dimensions.description: It is a user defined name applied to a given germplasm when it is mostly no longer segregating

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.location
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Location
dimensions.description: Breeding Location at which this field resides.The full name of this location as a string (e.g. Ackley, IA, USA)

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.location_cd
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Location Code
dimensions.description: A unique alpha identifier for a location.MIDAS reference ID for this location

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.market
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Market
dimensions.description: A specific market that the germplasm is being tested for sale. Used by Row Crop.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.maturity
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Maturity
dimensions.description: The target average relative maturity for the Entries in the Experiment

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.midas_field_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries MIDAS Field ID
dimensions.description: The MIDAS identifier that uniquely identifies the Field

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.midas_parent_plot_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries MIDAS Parent Plot ID

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.organization
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Organization
dimensions.description: The functional unit within the pipeline that is conducting the experiment such as Vegetable Manufacturing,Breeding etc

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.origin
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Origin
dimensions.description: Describes the parents used to generate a given line,

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.originator
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Originator
dimensions.description: Identifies the program which initiated the experiment

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.p360_product_id

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.pedigree
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Pedigree
dimensions.description: string version of parental ancestry.Basically represents different types of parental information for either inbreds or hybrids.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.planting_date
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Planting Date
dimensions.description: Planting date recorded at the field

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.planting_year
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Planting Year
dimensions.description: Year on which the plot was planted, formatted YYYY

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_barcode
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Barcode
dimensions.description: Its unique identifier.24 character, left padded, representation of the midas plot id starting with a "P"

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_coordinates
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Coordinates
dimensions.description: Sets of GPS coordinates of longitude and latitude pairs for the planned plots

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_deactivation_reason
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Deactivation Reason
dimensions.description: The reason the plot was deactivated

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_length
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Length
dimensions.description: The length of each plot in the field in meters

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_number
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Number
dimensions.description: A number assigned to a Plot within a Field, unique within the Field

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_subrow

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.plot_width
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Plot Width
dimensions.description: The width of each plot in the field in meters

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.previous_crop

dimensions.description: The crop that was planted in this Field's location in the previous year. This value can be used for processes such as volunteer monitoring, along with other things.

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.program
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Program
dimensions.description: The program which owns the experiment. This is the fts program code, or if its sourced from velocity the velocity group

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.protocol_id
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Protocol ID
dimensions.description: The unique identifier for a Protocol

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.protocol_name
dimensions.title: OPS Experiment Entries Protocol Name
dimensions.description: Name of associated protocol, it is the same as the MIRAGE protocol number

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.ranges_per_plot

dimensions.description: The default number of ranges (i.e., horizontal rows) to plant for a Repetition

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.region

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.repetition_column

dimensions.name: ops_experiment_entries.repetition_is_abandoned

dimensions.name: packaging_plan.input_barcode
dimensions.title: Packaging Plan Input Barcode
dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

cubes.name: pedlinev1
cubes.title: PedLine V1
cubes.description: PedLine stores information about crop lines, their traits, and parentage relationships in the breeding program. It captures genetic information, line attributes, and breeding history to support crop development and improvement.

measures.name: pedlinev1.count_distinct_line_id
measures.title: PedLine V1 Distinct Line Count
measures.description: Count of distinct line IDs in the pedline

measures.name: pedlinev1.count_distinct_base_line_id
measures.title: PedLine V1 Distinct Base Line Count
measures.description: Count of distinct base line IDs in the pedline

measures.name: pedlinev1.count_distinct_trait_lexicon_id
measures.title: PedLine V1 Distinct Trait Count
measures.description: Count of distinct trait lexicon IDs in the pedline

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length, ranging from 4-7 number of characters. Line Identifier. It is displayed as a number with no commas or spaces. It is generated in Global Row Crop Breeding applications.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.crop_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Crop ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length, ranging from 8 to 13 characters, and has a finite number of defined values based on current commercial crops of Bayer Crop Science.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.crop_name
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Crop Name
dimensions.description: Is a string representing the names of current commercial crops of Bayer Crop Science. It is displayed in proper case with some exceptions, and examples include Corn, Soybeans, and OSR-Canola.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_name
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line Name
dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length. Its displayed value can vary based on entity, with special characters placed throughout its content.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.base_line_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Base Line ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length, ranging from 4-7 number of characters. Parent Baseline Identifier.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.base_line_name
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Base Line Name
dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length, and represents the recurrent parent of the traited entity.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_type
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line Type
dimensions.description: Is a string representing the genetic homogeneity of a germplasm entity. Examples include: Inbred, Hybrid, SegPop.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_trait_name
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line Trait Name
dimensions.description: Is a string representing a commercial or precommercial trait. Examples include YGCB and RR2Y/VG.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_trait_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line Trait ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique integer representing a commercial or precommercial trait.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.line_traited_version_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Line Traited Version ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length, ranging from 6 to 9 characters. Primary Key of line traited version table in PedLine.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.p360_germplasm_group_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 P360 Germplasm Group ID
dimensions.description: Is a string value, a group associated to a germplasm

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.p360_product_synonym_group_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 P360 Product Synonym Group ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique product synonmym group identifier associated to the germplasm's group

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_ref_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Reference ID
dimensions.description: Text description of trait where traits defined individually and equal to LEXICON.COML_TRAIT_STACK2.STACK_ABBR when it is defined.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_code
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Code
dimensions.description: Three letter Manufacturing trait code matching the value defined in Lexicon.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_event_name
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Event Name
dimensions.description: Similar to EVENT_DISPLAY on germplasm, but including NATIVE traits.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_type
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Type
dimensions.description: Type of trait defined on table as COMM or PRECOMM.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_package
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Package
dimensions.description: Trait Package for the trait table record.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_sub_package
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Sub Package
dimensions.description: Trait Sub Package for the trait table record.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1.trait_lexicon_id
dimensions.title: PedLine V1 Trait Lexicon ID
dimensions.description: Linking ID to lexicon Data for a trait. Equal to LEXICON.COML_TRAIT_STACK2.COML_TRAIT_STACK_ID form ExaData.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_germplasm.germplasm_id
dimensions.title: Pedlinev1 Germplasm Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: Is a string value of variable length repersenting combination of germplasm_i, prod360_pop_id and preferred_line_entry_id.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_germplasm.prod360_pop_id
dimensions.title: Pedlinev1 Germplasm Prod360 Pop ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length. Represents the prod360PopId which is related to MIDAS germplasmId.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_germplasm.preferred_line_entry_id
dimensions.title: Pedlinev1 Germplasm Preferred Line Entry ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length. Primary key of preferred Line table in PedLine.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_germplasm.line_id
dimensions.title: Pedlinev1 Germplasm Line Id
dimensions.description: Line identifier that links to the main pedline table.

cubes.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes
cubes.title: PedLine Line Attributes
cubes.description: Is a unique string value of variable length repersenting combination of line attribute association and it's hierarchies.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length. Range from 4 to 5 characters. Line Attribute Identifier.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_ref_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Reference ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value of variable length of characters. Represents the shortened version of line attribute.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_value
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Value
dimensions.description: Is a unique string of variable length representing the transactional instance of the line attribute.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_level_name
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Level Name
dimensions.description: Is a unique value of variable length of characters. Represents the line attribute level.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_level_value
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Level Value
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length. Range from 4 to 8 characters.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_value_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Value ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length. Primary key of line attribute value table in PedLine.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_level_value_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Level Value ID
dimensions.description: Is a unique value integer of variable length. Primary Key of line attribute level value table in PedLine.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_attribute_data_type
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Attribute Data Type
dimensions.description: Is a value that specifies which type of value the attribute can hold.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_line_attributes.line_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Line Attributes Line Id
dimensions.description: Line identifier that links to the main pedline table.

cubes.name: pedlinev1_parentage
cubes.title: PedLine Parentage
cubes.description: Is a array value of variable length representing combination parentage information.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_line_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Line ID
dimensions.description: Parent Line Identifier, ranging from 4-7 number of characters.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_role
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Role
dimensions.description: Contribution of a given line as male (pollen donor) or female (ovule) parent.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_line_name
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Line Name
dimensions.description: Unique value string representing parent line.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_line_type
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Line Type
dimensions.description: Genetic homogeneity of parent germplasm entity (Inbred, Hybrid).

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_line_active
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Line Active
dimensions.description: Boolean indicating if parent line is active.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_base_line_id
dimensions.title: PedLine Parentage Parent Base Line ID
dimensions.description: Parent Baseline Identifier, ranging from 4-7 number of characters.

dimensions.name: pedlinev1_parentage.parent_base_line_name

dimensions.name: entries.set_entryId
dimensions.title: This contains Entries data from Velocity Velocity Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an entry in the Velocity application.  Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: entries.set_setId
dimensions.title: This contains Entries data from Velocity Velocity Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

cubes.name: sets_geography
cubes.title: Sets Geography
cubes.description: Set geography allows users to manage and organize their planting or growing activities based on specific locations.  This is particularly important in agricultural and controlled environment settings where different areas may have varying conditions, resources, or requirements.  By filtering and managing sets by location, users can ensure that they are optimizing their planting strategies and resources effectively. It helps users to focus on the specific geographic areas they are working with, leading to better planning and execution of their agricultural practices. It stores information for the Entry ID's that are part of Experiment Set Entries or Fields Trails

cubes.name: deployments
cubes.title: Corn Deployments
cubes.description: The depolyment view provides key information across various key metrics like Density, By Location, H2H Agronomics,  H2H Artificial Greensnap, H2H Disease, H2H Maturity, H2H Yield for a given head product. It helps users to view the performance pf heads against checks. Bio Economic Index (BEI) - Demonstrates strength of product fit for yield/moisture and agronomic traits by product segment.                 By Location - Provides more information related to Yield Performance, Agronomic, and Stress.  Uses current year by location data to show the trend of entry compared with check mean against the set mean and for performance the average win-rate across locations versus check mean. Density -  Is based on an integrated-density-testing (IDT) scheme that uses the standard GXE set as the mid density and, relative to it at a location level, includes a high density set (+5K PPA) and a low density set (-5K PPA).  The high and low sets are paired with standard GXE at 20 locations in core RMs, and 14 locations in other RMs (5 for RM70-80).   For the year - 2024, each set only contains 2 to 3 checks.  BLUP analysis predicts relative density response interaction and overall hybrid performance by density. H2H Agronomics - It shares performance information about the key characteristics like Test Weight, Root Lodging, Stalk Lodging, Plant Height, Ear Height, CCRVIG H2H Artificial Greensnap - Measures potential for greensnap based on artificial induction. H2H Maturity - It shares key information about Moisture,  S50, P50 etc.. H2H Disease - It shares key information of head product against check for different disease rating point like GLS, NCLB, Goss' Wilt, ASR, Tar Spot, Southern Rust etc H2H Yield  Performance of head against selected checks or all of the checks. Product - It's all the head product  and its precommcial product names

cubes.name: edited_allele_analysis
cubes.title: Edited Allele Analysis
cubes.description: A combined view of EditedAlleleCallID, EditedAlleleID, and SMEv2SEQProject_meta_data to provide a unified dataset for allele analysis and sequencing project metadata.

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_call_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.sum_of_allele_call_read_count
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Total Allele Call Reads
measures.description: This is to get sum of Allele Call Read Counts

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_seqlims_project
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Sequence Project
measures.description: This is to get distinct count of Sequence Project

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_call_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele Call ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of Sample ID Product 360 (p360) curated reference assembly including the chromosome or contig pollux ID identifying the guide used coordinate of the guide on the reference assembly and local_CIGAR. This makes this effectively a UUID for SME2.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sample_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sample ID
dimensions.description: The Sample ID as designated by the LIMS system note is a concatenation of underscore separated SEQID and sample number.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.call_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.barcode
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Barcode
dimensions.description: Barcode refers to the plant barcode or gds barcode as provided from LIMS and importantly is sample specific.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.reagent
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reagent
dimensions.description: This generally refers to constructs or pMONs but in the future could indicate other methodologies for introducing foreign DNA.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.guide_name
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Guide Name
dimensions.description: Pollux ID from SeqUR for the guide used to create this edit.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_read_count
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Read Counts
dimensions.description: Count of reads with this allele call covering the guide window.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.percent_of_reads_covering_guide
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Percent Reads
dimensions.description: Percentage of reads covering the guide with this exact allele. Calculated as allele_call_read_count over total_reads_covering_guide.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.hamming_distance
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Hamming Distance
dimensions.description: Number of differences between two sequences of the same length in this case the reference sequence and aligned read sequence.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.seqlims_project
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project
dimensions.description: SEQID is the discrete unit of projects that go through the sequencing lab and groups a set of samples that were sequenced together in a library.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_run
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Run ID
dimensions.description: The run identifier from the sequencer that this project was ran on for backtracking and unifying with sequencing QC.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_included
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Included
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were above the minimum required threshold (and met QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_excluded
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Excluded
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were not above the minimum required threshold (or did not meet other QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.analysis_cutoff_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Analysis Cutoff Used
dimensions.description: A float used to cutoff the analysis and keep noise due to sequencing error out of the results.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.min_reads_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Min Reads Used
dimensions.description: The minimum number of reads that must be present for a sample to be retained in the results otherwise filtered out.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_project_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of reference name identifier with chromosome (contig) 5' coordinate start of guide and local CIGAR.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_type
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Type
dimensions.description: Type of allele, one of 'edit', 'wt', or 'offsite'.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.fp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Five Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Five prime sequence which is the sequence upstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.tp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Three Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Three prime sequence which is the sequence downstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.ref_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference string
dimensions.description: The wild-type or reference sequence of the guide region.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.match_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Match string
dimensions.description: The sequence of the read aligned segment for the allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: Compact idiosyncratic gapped alignment report for the entire read with respect to the edited allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.local_CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: The CIGAR localized to the guide region including notation for contiguous edits outside the guide window.
dimensions.shortTitle: Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)

cubes.name: location360
cubes.title: Weather(TWC)
cubes.description: The Weather Company (TWC) historical weather data provides a global coverage for Bayer area of interest from 1979 to present. Location360 is collaborating with The Climate Corporation (TCC) on building this historical weather data archive.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest temperature recorded during the day. Also called min temp, daily low temp, lowest temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest temperature recorded during the day. Also called max temp, daily high temp, peak temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_midpoint_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Midpoint Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the midpoint between daily max and min temperatures. Also called mid temp, temperature midpoint, average extreme temp.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average temperature. Also called mean temp, daily mean temperature, average temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called max dew point, peak dew point, daily high dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called min dew point, daily low dew point, lowest dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Minimum Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average dew point temperature. Also called mean dew point, average dew point, daily mean dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Average Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum wind speed recorded during the day. Also called max wind, peak wind speed, daily high wind.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum wind speed recorded during the day. Also called min wind, daily low wind, lowest wind speed.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind speed. Also called mean wind, average wind speed, daily mean wind.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind speed measured at 2 meters above ground. Also called avg wind 2m, wind speed 2m avg, mean wind 2m.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Average Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum wind speed at 2 meters above ground. Also called min wind 2m, lowest wind 2m, wind speed 2m min.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum wind speed at 2 meters above ground. Also called max wind 2m, peak wind 2m, wind speed 2m max.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_gust
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Gust
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest wind gust recorded during the day. Also called max gust, peak wind gust, daily high gust.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_direction
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Direction
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind direction over the day (in degrees). Also called mean wind direction, wind dir avg, average wind bearing.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called max rh, peak humidity, daily high humidity, maximum relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called min rh, daily low humidity, lowest humidity, minimum relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average relative humidity. Also called mean rh, average humidity, daily mean relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called max pressure, peak pressure, daily high pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called min pressure, daily low pressure, lowest pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average atmospheric pressure. Also called mean pressure, average pressure, daily mean pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_total_precipitation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Total Precipitation
measures.description: It is the average value of the total precipitation (rainfall/snowfall) during the day. Also called precip total, daily rainfall, total rain, precipitation.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_downward_solar_radiation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Downward Solar Radiation
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum solar radiation received at the surface. Also called max solar radiation, peak solar flux, daily high solar radiation.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Downward Solar Radiation

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_total_downward_solar_radiation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Total Downward Solar Radiation
measures.description: It is the average value of the total solar radiation received during the day. Also called total solar radiation, solar flux total, daily solar energy.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Total Downward Solar Radiation

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_eto
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Evapotranspiration (ETO)
measures.description: It is the average value of the reference evapotranspiration (ETo) for the day. Also called eto, evapotranspiration reference, daily eto value.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_etr
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Evapotranspiration (ETR)
measures.description: It is the average value of the radiation-based evapotranspiration (ETr) for the day. Also called etr, evapotranspiration radiation, daily etr value.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_day_length
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Day Length
measures.description: It is the average value of the duration of daylight hours for the day. Also called daylight hours, sunlight duration, daily sun hours.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest temperature recorded during the day. Also called Min Temp, Daily Low Temp, Lowest Temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Maximum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest temperature recorded during the day. Also called Max Temp, Daily High Temp, Peak Temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called Min Dew Point Temp.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Maximum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called Max Dew Point Temp.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_avg_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the mean wind speed over the day. Also called Avg Wind Speed.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest wind speed recorded during the day. Also called Min Wind Speed.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Maximum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest wind speed recorded during the day. Also called Max Wind Speed.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_avg_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the mean relative humidity over the day. Also called Avg RH.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called Min RH.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Maximum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called Max RH.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_avg_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the mean atmospheric pressure over the day. Also called Avg Pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called Min Pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Maximum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called Max Pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_total_precipitation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Precipitation Total
measures.description: It is the average value of the total amount of precipitation recorded during the day. Also called Rainfall Total.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_freq_precip_01mm
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Precipitation at 0.1mm
measures.description: It is the average number of times precipitation was at least 0.1mm.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_freq_precip_02mm
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Precipitation at 0.2mm
measures.description: It is the average number of times precipitation was at least 0.2mm.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_freq_precip_05mm
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Precipitation at 0.5mm
measures.description: It is the average number of times precipitation was at least 0.5mm.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_freq_precip_10mm
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Precipitation at 1.0mm
measures.description: It is the average number of times precipitation was at least 1.0mm.

dimensions.name: location360.grid_id
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) Grid ID
dimensions.description: Unique identifier for the spatial grid cell where data is collected. Also called as location id, spatial cell id, region code, grid cell

dimensions.name: location360.Within_Distance
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) Within distance
dimensions.description: This is derived from Geometry Spatial using ST_GEOGPOINT

dimensions.name: location360.daily_date
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) Daily Date
dimensions.description: The calendar date corresponding to the daily weather measurements. Also called date, observation date, record date, day

dimensions.name: location360.day_of_year
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) Day of Year
dimensions.description: The day in the year (Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Saturday Sunday). It is also called as DOY, today, Day Name

dimensions.name: location360.l0_name
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) L0 Region Name
dimensions.description: High-level region name, typically country or similar. Other names are Country, Global Region, Region Level 0, L0 Region

dimensions.name: location360.l1_name
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) L1 Region Name
dimensions.description: Mid-level region name, typically state or similar. Other names are State, Province, Region Level 1, L1 Region

dimensions.name: location360.l2_name
dimensions.title: Weather(TWC) L2 Region Name
dimensions.description: Lower-level region name, typically county or similar. Other names are County, District, Region Level 2, L2 Region

cubes.name: seed_processing
cubes.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing
cubes.description: Seed processing is the first step in the process of preparing seeds for planting post harvest.  The main goal is to enhance seed quality while also gathering quantity and sizing data.  This process can include shelling, cleaning, sorting, sizing, counting and treating seed. The current source for seed information is Shellmatic. Shellmatic is  IT system that enables overall Seed Processing system

dimensions.description: Is an integer value which represents the MIDAS Application Group ID with default value as 0.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It is displayed as '879556730357452'. It is a seed treater. This applies seed treatment to seed

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treatment_name
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Name
dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length alphabets and special characters, with an upper limit of 255 characters.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It represents the name of treatment applied to the batch.  It is displayed as 'CL/MX for US/LAN (Poncho)'.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_volume
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Pump Volume
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment applied to the batch in mL.  It is generated from the shellmatic 3 PC application. It is displayed as '21.9384' It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_dry_time
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Dry Time
dimensions.description: Is a variable length field storing an integer value. It represents the amount of time in seconds the batch is allowed to dry. It is displayed as '80'. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_speed
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Pump Seed
dimensions.description: Is a floating point value that represents the RPM setting of the treater pump used for the batch.  It is generated from the settings file of the application. It is displayed as '150'.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_vol_per_rev
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Volume Per Revolution
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment delivered with each revolution of the pump in mL.  Treater pump volume per revolution is generated from the settings file of the shelmatic and can be calibrated by the application. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_treatment_rate

dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment to be applied per 1000 seeds.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It is displayed as '0.0. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_setId

Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_entryId

dimensions.name: seed_processing.protocol_id

dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.protocol_name

dimensions.name: seed_processing.germplasm_id

dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.velmat_material_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Velocity Material ID
dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.access_growergroups

dimensions.name: seed_processing.access_usergroups

dimensions.name: seed_processing.relative_maturity
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.sets_material_id

dimensions.name: seed_processing.population_id

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_name

Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.line_type

dimensions.name: seed_processing.line_code

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pedigree

dimensions.name: seed_processing.origin

dimensions.name: seed_processing.catalog_id

It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: seed_processing.catalog_seed_type

dimensions.name: seed_processing.p360_product_id
